window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>“BEST NONFICTION BOOK OF THE 20TH CENTURY.” —</b><b><i>Time</i></b></p> <p><b>Volume 1 of the gripping epic masterpiece, Solzhenitsyn's chilling report of his arrest and interrogation, which exposed to the world the vast bureaucracy of secret police that haunted Soviet society. Features a new foreword by Anne Applebaum.</b></p> <p>“The greatest and most powerful single indictment of a political regime ever leveled in modern times.” —George F. Kennan</p> <p>“It is impossible to name a book that had a greater effect on the political and moral consciousness of the late twentieth century.” —David Remnick, <i>The New Yorker</i></p> <p>“Solzhenitsyn’s masterpiece. . . . <i>The Gulag Archipelago</i> helped create the world we live in today.” —Anne Applebaum, Pulitzer Prize-winning author of <i>Gulag: A History</i>, from the foreword</p>"; 
